.TH BUDDYDRIVE-RELAY 1 "April 2025" "BuddyDrive"
.SH NAME
buddydrive-relay \- TCP relay server for BuddyDrive P2P connections
.SH DESCRIPTION
BuddyDrive Relay is a simple TCP relay server that enables BuddyDrive peers to communicate when direct peer-to-peer connections aren't possible due to NAT or firewall restrictions.
.PP
The relay server:
.IP \(bu 2
Accepts connections from two peers with matching tokens
.IP \(bu 2
Validates tokens against a whitelist
.IP \(bu 2
Relays data bidirectionally between paired peers
.IP \(bu 2
Automatically disconnects when either peer leaves
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B buddydrive-relay
[port]
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I port
Port to listen on (default: 41722)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BUDDYDRIVE_TOKENS
Comma-separated list of allowed tokens. Example:
.EX
export BUDDYDRIVE_TOKENS="swift-eagle,brave-moose,calm-river"
.EE
.SH PROTOCOL
.PP
.nf
Client -> Server: <token>\\n
Server -> Client: OK\\n           (when paired)
Server -> Client: WAIT\\n         (waiting for peer)
Server -> Client: (disconnect)   (invalid token)
.fi
.PP
After OK, all data is relayed bidirectionally.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run with default port:
buddydrive-relay
.TP
Run on custom port:
buddydrive-relay 41722
.TP
With Docker:
docker run -d -p 41722:41722 -e BUDDYDRIVE_TOKENS="swift-eagle" buddydrive-relay
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR buddydrive(1),
.BR buddydrive-gui(1)
